// The Cellar Restaurant Strings The Cellar 4.8 About At the Cellar we offer just one tasting menu, inspired by seasonal Scottish produce and locally foraged ingredients from our coastline and countryside. We work passionately with local farmers, suppliers and producers, to bring our guests the best produce available to us throughout the seasons, enabling us to create a purposefully designed and thoughtful dinning experience. Venue Type Restaurant
// The Gannet Restaurant Strings The Gannet 4.7 The restaurant was named during a research trip to the Outer Hebrides where the iconic seafaring bird holds a special place in local tradition. We were taken by its unique look, ability to hunt and being a reference to those of us with robust appetites. At the Gannet we serve a seasonally changing multi-course menu inspired by our network of small artisan producers, foragers and farmers.
// The Cail Bruich Restaurant Strings Cail Bruich 4.25 Chef Lorna McNee and the team work closely with producers and suppliers to offer guests the highest quality food and drink. We offer our chef\'s tasting menu that changes in harmony with the Scottish seasons, dictated by ingredients that are local and Sustainable, and may even come from our own kitchen garden.
